    "body" : "<blockquote>\n  <p>should use object == null over Objects.isNull() in a if statement?</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>If you look at the <a href=\"http://grepcode.com/file/repository.grepcode.com/java/root/jdk/openjdk/8-b132/java/util/Objects.java#Objects.isNull%28java.lang.Object%29\" rel=\"noreferrer\">source code</a> of <code>IsNull</code> method,</p>\n\n<pre><code> /* Returns true if the provided reference is null otherwise returns false.*/\n\n public static boolean isNull(Object obj) {\n     return obj == null;\n }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>It is the same. There is no difference. So you can use it safely.</p>\n"
