      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I would disagree on the claim that it is &quot;much easier/clearer to write&quot;.   1. It is not more concise.   2. It is obviously less expressive, especially for those not familiar with latest Java syntax.    For me as someone who is not writing Java on daily basis (I write Scala) it feels hallucinatory having a static method which does nothing but checking for null.  This method is just a distruction from fluent code reading without any benifits added."
