      "comment_id" : 134306985,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@EliGolin While I agree with your readability points, there is also a (very slight) performance benefit to not using Lambda expressions here. That is, the program won&#39;t have to define and instantiate a new anonymous method, both of which have (very slight) memory/compute overhead compared to just passing <code>isNull</code>. Slight as this overhead is, it adds up over all the Stream expressions in your codebase. For this reason alone, I always default to <code>isNull</code> syntax in Streams (<i>not</i> in other contexts like if statements)."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 4914349,
        "reputation" : 2574,
        "user_id" : 3991688,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 69,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/28a449026a2de59dcbea4da40d8dd4a1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
