      "comment_id" : 139447903,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Is it just me, or are lambdas like &quot;x -&gt; x == null&quot; always easier to read than &quot;Objects::isNull&quot;? I don&#39;t know why they added the :: syntax? Does it save a method call?"
