      "creation_date" : 1728885606,
      "post_id" : 60523951,
      "comment_id" : 139447909,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "This one is actually decent. But writing the full Objects.IsNull feels like code bloat.  Regarding CPU cycles. It might matter in a very tight loop in a 3D game, but does absolutely not matter in your regular backend code. An unfortunate result of fluent syntax in general is that you end up with complex objects and a lot of unnecessary method calls. Because these languages where not designed with fluent syntax in mind."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
